Defendant Daniel P Bath in court with attorney Bradley J. Bloch.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court addresses defendant's pro se letters.  Court denies defendant's request to have Attorney Bloch removed as counsel and for Judge Maxwell to recuse himself.  State presents arguments.  Defense counsel and defendant presents arguments.  Court imposes the following sentence:

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS JAIL (CREDIT - 0 days)

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with:  any of the victims in any way or though a third-party, unless authorized by agent.

RESTITUTION:  $2,771.94 to Val S. and $1,184.00 to Viktoria S. (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DRGOD:  $10.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation).

Defendant is eligible for early termination upon all fines and resitutions being paid.
